  "doc_id": "45451",
  "text": "Our case underwent total surgical excision. During surgical excision, a urologist was included in the operative team because of the close vicinity of the mass to the urethra. A Foley catheter was inserted through the urethra and the mass was then totally excised. The mass was easily dissected from neighboring tissues. Since the mass was localized within subcutaneous tissue away from any vascular structures, minimal bleeding occurred. However, if the mass extends into the vicinity of the clitoris and anus, the inferior haemorrhoidal and clitoral branches of the pudendal vessels may be traumatized leading to bleeding episodes. Haemostatic sutures should be used in cases of diffuse bleeding [CITATION_1] .",
